  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ Gas 6</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop the <strong>carrots</strong> into chips, then cut the <strong>potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> (skins on)  into similar sized chips</p><p>Add the <strong>carrot and</strong> <strong>potato chips</strong> to a baking tray with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> half </strong>the <strong>smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657627432960-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657627432960-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657627432960-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657627432960-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657627432960-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetable chips are cooking, combine the <strong>lamb mince</strong>, <strong>ras el hanout</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>lamb mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657627437564-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657627437564-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657627437564-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657627437564-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657627437564-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap the <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, then cut into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> rectangles and add them to a baking tray lined with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>lamb mix</strong> into the centre of the pastry rectangles, lengthways in a sausage shape</p><p>Press the meat down a little with your fingers to flatten it slightly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657627440935-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657627440935-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657627440935-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657627440935-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657627440935-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Brush a little <strong>cold water </strong>around the edges of the pastry</p><p>Fold the pastry over the mixture and press it together with your fingers to seal in the meat with as little air trapped inside as possible</p><p>Crimp and seal the edges with a fork – these are your <strong>spiced lamb sausage rolls</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
